sectioned_description.interaction:

We collaborate with other houses in Havana and other places of great interest like Varadero, Trinidad, Vinales, Cienfuego, Santiago de Cuba and many others
sectioned_description.description:
Cuban house in Havana that offers its guests a very special environment where taste and tradition come together in a magic look "all white" Located in the most ancient part of the Malecon Habanero, seafront and within walking distance of Old Havana

The White House is a colonial traditional one that is ideally located on the famous seafront El Malecón-Havana, which offers stunning views from the Havana Bay. It’s only 15 minutes walk from the old district Habana Vieja, which combines historical heritage with the decadent charm of its streets and the jubilant joy of its neighbors.  Also very close is another district, El Vedado, that it’s known for the art deco style buildings and its vibrant nightlife, full of bars, clubs, cabarets, and restaurants of international renown. The beaches are just 20 minutes by car to the east of Havana city. 
The decoration of the house includes, among other things, some 19th century Cuban furniture and huge mirrors from the 50th, combined with others of contemporary design and natural fiber fabrics. The most of them in white, those give to the visitors sensations of relaxation, wellness and comfort. 
The 100 m2 apartment is distributed as follows: a long balcony in front and a big living-dining room where the guests can have breakfasts or even dinners with fantastic views to the sea; a well equipped kitchen for the staff prepares the meals; and three rooms on the left side of the house. All them have windows with natural light and lateral views to the sea. There are two doubles and one is triple. They are comfortable provided with air conditioner, mini bar, wardrobe, towels, bedding and its own private bathroom. 
There are many reasons why we invite you to come and enjoy an unforgettable holiday in our place. You mustn't miss this unique experience. The magic of Cuba is waiting for you.

Change of sheets and towels every other day or convenience of tenants
 night custodian
 Information is provided to the client in Spanish, English and Italian

 Services upon request:
 dinner service
 breakfast service
 Laundry service
 taxi service
 bar service and minibar

During the day owners and house staff are at your disposal for any request or provide information about your stay.
 Independence and privacy are guaranteed.
We collaborate with other houses in Havana and other places of great interest like Varadero, Trinidad, Vinales, Cienfuego, Santiago de Cuba and many others

MALECON
 Very conveniently located for visiting all major sights.
 Everyone who loves peace, walking outdoors enjoying a wonderful view of the Caribbean sea, here you can do it.

We are located near the History Center of the town (Habana Vieja was declared a UNESCO World Heritage Site), if you like walking could visit in just 10-15 min walk:
Museum of the Revolution: is housed in what was the Presidential Palace of all Cuban presidents 
Memorial Gramma: is a yacht that was used to transport the fighters of the cuban Revolution from Mexico to Cuba 
Museum of Fine Arts of Havana: is a museum that exhibits art collections from the colonial times up to contemporary generations
Capitol: was the seat of government in Cuba until after the Cuban Revolution in 1959, its design and name recall the United States Capitol in Washington DC
National Theater Garcia Lorca. Located in the Paseo del Prado in Havana, it has been home of the Cuban Ballet and, on its main stage, of the International Ballet Festival of Havana
Havana Cathedral Square: One of eleven Roman Catholic cathedrals on the island of Cuba
Floridita Bar – Restaurant La Cuna del Daiquiri: famous for its Daiquiri cocktails and for having been one of the favorite hangouts of Ernest Hemingway in Havana located in the end of Calle Obispo
Bodeguita del Medio: famous destination. It lays claim to being the birthplace of Mojito cocktail 
If you prefer to take a taxi or have a car is all very close. Around house you can park your car in complete safety.

Discovery with us Havana from Cubans, we will show the places, dining and Cuban fashion.
 Come visit us !!!!!

sorted_reviews.comments: Yosany's Place was absolutely positively exquisite! It is a true example of how resourceful the Cuban people are. Dont be surprised if when you arrive you are not sure you have come to the right place. That is the delight! Painted wrought iron railings and chipped marble stairs lead you to the third floor along vintage subway tiles. Knock on the door and the most lovely staff welcome you into a light fill exquisite living space with stunning views of the Malecon and the sea. The hospitality here is delightful. Our room was small but very clean and smelled fresh and sweet. The breakfast was quite affordable and delicious. I will definitely visit again and also try the White House #2.

THIS PLACE IS OUTSTANDING!  Our favorite throughout our entire trip. It is a bit more expensive than other options but completely worth it. Located directly on El Malecon with a balcony overlooking the ocean.  Drinks served as soon as you get there by their wonderful host Enedys.  We had a private room and private bathroom with a safe.  Enedys was in the house but kept completely to herself the entire time unless we asked her to make us drinks or help with recommendations (or just to hang out with us because she was so great).  The place as a whole is open and airy and beautiful.  We felt completely safe the entire time and wished we had booked it for the whole trip.  Easy walk to Old Havana, easy cab to Vedado and plenty of bars and restaurants around. Even a restaurant from Diners Drive Ins and Dives on the Food Network directly next door!

WiFi was accessible at the park next door or the hotel one block away where they also sell the internet cards.  

Cabs drive by constantly and are easy to hail and Enedys will help if you'd like!

Overall an excellent experience and one that blew the other four places we stayed out of the water!  WILL DEFINITELY RETURN!!!

The house is in a great location with a beautiful view. Having a host on location was a plus. Be prepared for the all white decor, especially in the bathroom. Overall Yosvany’s place was well worth the price.

Staying at “Casa Blanca” made our trip to Cuba even more special. First of all the customer service is superb. Yosvany, his sisters Ana and Yanet + his entire team are GREAT! They were very cordial and helpful. Yosvany helped me to surprise my husband by getting a delicious tres leches cake for his birthday. After a few days of walking around and touring the City we realized that the location of Casa Blanca in the center of Havana was a blessing (we saved a lot on taxi money) because we were at walking distance (15-20 minutes) to a lot of places like Central Park where there is a lot of action and things to do + Casa Blanca is right by the famous Malecon and offers amazing ocean views, to your left the City and to the right El Castillo de Los Tres Reyes del Morro. At Casa Blanca we had a lot of conveniences: hot water, a safe box in our room, a small refrigerator that for our convenience was refilled every day with bottled water, juices and Cuban beer for a small price. They cleaned and made our bed every day. They arranged transportation from and to the airport and they also arranged a classic car to take us round trip the night we went to Cabaret Tropicana (excellent show). We stayed in Casa Blanca 8 days and we can definitely call Casa Blanca our home in Cuba. We are planning to visit next year and we are definitely staying there. We want to thank Yosvany and his team for making our vacation the best we ever had. Good luck and continue the great job! ~ Mara & Jaime.
Beautiful and stylish space in a nice location facing the ocean. All hosts are very friendly and helpful.

BEYOND GORGEOUS HOME! Anita is one of the few hostess at the location, she was exceptional, very warm and attentive. The location is stunning, all white, vintage esthetic, and located infront of havanas malecón. It is a stunning view, truly out of a movie❤️ the apartment was very clean and lively with music playing all through out the day ;) they offer a good breakfast at a cheap
Price. I highly recommend BREAKFAST and staying at this location it'll
Make for stunning photos!

sectioned_description.description:
un luogo ameno

Our country house consists of a large kitchen - living room, two double bedrooms and one single bedroom and 2 bathrooms.

Besides that, outside, there is a nice veranda and garden to enjoy and relax. 

The country house is located in Canicattì.

It is only 20 min. from the sea and 2 min. by car from the center of Canicattì, where you will find bars, supermarkets, pizzerias, restaurants, bank, railway station etc. Canicattì is a town of 35 000 inhabitants 30 km from Agrigento, Caltanissetta to 30 km, 170 km and 180 km from Catania to Palermo.

We provide on demand a special breakfast with aperitifs and varied, genuine local products as well as our homemade jams. Also on demand we can also serve you dinner. We provide wi-fi, parking spot, indoor fireplace and airconditioned ambient.

sorted_reviews.comments: This is our second visit to Antonio. We actually returned to Sicily to visit Antonio and Samir. A special surprise was Kawsar, a young man who was gentle and kind from Bengal. We felt at home and completely taken care of. Our days were planned and our trips were guided expertly by Samir and Antonio. Dinners at the house were abundant and delicious. The conversation always meaningful and full of warmth and laughter.  The house is a traditional Sicilian house- full of charm and lovely. It is a place for people who want an intimate Sicilian experience and interactions with others. We feel like we have a family and a home in Sicily.

Our experience with Antonio was as described by other guests. We booked same day and despite this Antonio was able to welcome us with a delicious multiple course meal that we enjoyed on his beautiful porch. We highly recommend!

Many thanks given to Antonio for opening his lovely country home to these tired travelers. He is a marvelous cook who treated us with great respect. He took time to give us ideas about important sights to see and made sure we knew how to get around as well. Highlight of our trip to Sicily!

sorted_reviews.comments: Don't miss the 10 course meal that Antonio cooks. His heart is in the meal. Lovely location and comfortable. His cooking is 10 stars+. Antonio is the most gracious host. We will return!!

This was the ultimate Italian experience for us! Antonio made us dinner the night we were there. Eight courses with wine and fabulous conversations!!  We got there earlier than expected, and I don't think he was ready for us, but he was extremely gracious, made us a cheese plate and poured us some lovely refreshing wine! Then he told us about the greek temples we could visit while he finished getting ready for us. (they were amazing). I slept in my most comfortable bed of the entire trip. If you get chance to stay here, do, he was a wonderful host!

Our stay with Antonio was lovely.  His home is beautiful and just as pictured with pretty gardens and a great outdoor dining area.  He was so helpful, suggesting we visit Agrigento's temples in the evening rather than the heat of the next day.  His multi course home cooked dinner was a work of art-  Sicilian cooking with flair and love.  Come hungry!!
